---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Mail } from "lucide-react";

const title = "Privacy Policy | ReloFinder.ch";
const description =
  "Our commitment to protecting your personal data. Learn how ReloFinder collects, uses, and safeguards your information.";
const canonical = "https://relofinder.ch/privacy";
const lastUpdated = "February 28, 2026";

const combinedSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      itemListElement: [
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          position: 1,
          name: "Home",
          item: "https://relofinder.ch",
        },
        {
          "@type": "ListItem",
          position: 2,
          name: "Privacy Policy",
          item: "https://relofinder.ch/privacy",
        },
      ],
    },
    {
      "@type": "WebPage",
      name: title,
      description: description,
      url: canonical,
      datePublished: "2026-02-28",
      dateModified: "2026-02-28",
    },
  ],
};
---

<Layout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonical={canonical}
  schema={combinedSchema}
>
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 prose prose-slate">
    <span
      class="inline-block py-1 px-3 rounded-full bg-gray-100 text-gray-600 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-6 not-prose"
    >
      Legal
    </span>
    <h1
      class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight"
    >
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>
    <div
      class="flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-500 text-sm border-b border-gray-100 pb-8 mb-8 not-prose"
    >
      <span>Last Updated: {lastUpdated}</span>
    </div>

    <p>
      ReloFinder.ch is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring
      transparent handling of your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains
      how we collect, use, process, and protect your information when you use
      our relocation services platform.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Data Controller</h2>
    <p>
      The primary controller responsible for your personal data and operator of
      the ReloFinder platform is:
    </p>
    <div
      class="not-prose bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-xl border border-gray-100 my-8"
    >
      <p class="font-bold text-gray-900">Expat Digital Group LLC</p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-1 mb-4">
        1209 MOUNTAIN ROAD PL NE STE N<br />
        ALBUQUERQUE, BERNALILLO COUNTY, NM 87110 USA
      </p>

      <div
        class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200"
      >
        <a
          href="mailto:hello@relofinder.ch"
          class="flex items-center text-sm font-bold text-gray-900 hover:text-[#FF6F61] transition-colors"
        >
          <Mail className="w-4 h-4 mr-2" />
          hello@relofinder.ch
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <h3>Personal Information</h3>
    <p>
      We may collect the following types of personal information when you use
      our services:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Contact Details:</strong> Name, email address, phone number.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Relocation Data:</strong> Requirements, preferences, move dates, family
        composition.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Communication Data:</strong> Messages, correspondence, and feedback.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Corporate Data:</strong> Company details for our B2B clients.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Usage Information</h3>
    <p>
      We automatically collect certain information about your device and how you
      interact with our website:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address and browser type.</li>
      <li>Device information and operating system.</li>
      <li>Pages visited, time spent, and referring URL.</li>
      <li>Cookies and similar tracking technologies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>We process your data for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Service Delivery:</strong> To match you with verified relocation providers
        and facilitate quotes.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Communication:</strong> To respond to your inquiries and provide support.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Improvement:</strong> To analyze usage patterns and enhance our platform's
        user experience.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Compliance:</strong> To meet legal and regulatory obligations.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Sharing & Third Parties</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell your personal data. We may share your information with:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Service Providers:</strong> Verified relocation agencies you explicitly
        choose to connect with.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Technical Partners:</strong> Hosting, analytics, and email service
        providers (under strict data processing agreements).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Legal Authorities:</strong> When required by law or to protect our
        rights.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>Under applicable data protection laws, you have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access the personal data we hold about you.</li>
      <li>Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
      <li>Request deletion of your data ("Right to be Forgotten").</li>
      <li>Object to the processing of your data.</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent at any time.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      To exercise any of these rights, please contact our privacy team at <a
        href="mailto:hello@relofinder.ch">hello@relofinder.ch</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
      We implement robust technical and organizational measures to protect your
      data, including SSL encryption, secure servers, and strict access
      controls. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100%
      secure.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Updates to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The latest version
      will always be posted on this page with the effective date.
    </p>
  </main>
</Layout>
